    <note>Yang(2) Huizhi [12941] Fujian TZ, 146.8b; Su Song, WJ, 51.1a-10b; Yang Yi, WJ, 11.17a-23b. CBD has as Yi(3)'s [7097] younger cousin, but consideration of Wenyi's [12947] (q.v.) funerary inscription (Yi(3)'s grandfather) and that of Huizhi makes it clear that Huizi was Yi(3)'s second granduncle (Huizhi was the son of Yi(3)'s great grandfather Bi(2)'s [12946] brother Chen(3) [12938]). He had no sons and his only brother was married to Song(2) Gao [12940], father of Shou [1575], who was the recipient of his maternal grandfather's library and initially entered the civil service when granted an office when Huizhi died.  CBD, 4, 3193-4. 《唐代人物知識ベース》記其生卒年為：921 - 1000.</note>
